# Markdown Formatting Standards

## Table Formatting
- Use proper markdown tables instead of ASCII art diagrams
- Tables should be clean and readable with consistent column alignment
- Include clear headers and descriptions for complex tables

## Code Blocks
- Use proper markdown code blocks with language specification
- For shell commands: ```shell
- For Java code: ```java
- For configuration files: ```toml

## Images
- Reference images using relative paths: `../images/posts/filename.png`
- Include alt text for accessibility
- Use descriptive filenames

## Frontmatter
All markdown posts should include proper frontmatter:
```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"
date: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ
toc: true
tags:
  - tag1
  - tag2
pdf: true
---
```

## Multilingual Content
- Maintain identical structure between English and Italian versions
- Keep the same images, code examples, and formatting
- Only translate the text content, not the technical elements
